dding:10px 0px 0px 0px;">The rich history of the city is at your students' fingertips. Between a thrilling vertical shuttle ride, amazing multimedia exhibits and, of course, the view, they may not know they're learning while having this much fun.</p><p style="padding:10px 0px 0px 0px;"><a href="pdf/TeacherGuidePDF_Final.pdf" target="_blank">Click here</a> to download our specially created Teacher's Guide to start planning your lessons from Top of the Rock.</p><p style="padding:10px 0px 0px 0px;">Then, call 212-698-2000 to learn about our special school group rates and to start planning your field trip to the Top. All school groups and camps who visit us enjoy a dedicated entrance, a VIP ambassador to greet them, and reserved ticket times so there are never long lines or waits.</p><div style="position:absolute;left:700px;top:310px;">  <a href="#" onclick="disclaim();return false;">*Disclaimer</a></div>		    <div id="disclaimer"><p style="padding:10px 0px 0px 0px;">All TOP OF THE ROCK<sup>TM</sup> Education Program materials are protected by copyright and are provided for use only by students and educators in connection with fieldtrips to the TOP OF THE ROCK<sup>TM</sup> Observation Deck. No commercial use, reproduction or distribution is permitted. By downloading this information, you hereby agree to the foregoing terms and conditions.</p><br /><a href="#" onClick="closeDis()">Close X</a></div>                       </div>                </div>     <div class="groupsTeachersBig" style="top:63px;left:460px;"></div>     </div></asp:Content>